p.-text
  | Popovers provide an contextual space, attached to an element and in an upper z-index layer, where you can
  | include any kind of HTML code related to the trigger.

h3 Base
p.-text
  | To render a popover, add your HTML code to a <code>data-popover-content</code> attribute. Then,
  | you can initialize it with the chi.popover factory method.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    button(data-popover-content='<div class="-px--2"><h4>Popover!</h4><p>This is a popover content triggered by a button. </p></div>').a-btn.-mr--2 Popover
  :code(lang='html')
    <button id='popover-1' class="a-btn" data-popover-content='<div class="-px--2"><h4>Popover!</h4><p>This is a popover content triggered by a button. </p></div>'>Popover</button>
    <script>chi.popover(document.getElementById('popover-1'));</script>

h3 Positioning
p.-text
